class FoodRatings {
    constructor(foods, cuisines, ratings) {
        this.food_ratings = new Map();
        this.highest_rated = new Map();

        for (let i = 0; i < foods.length; ++i) {
            this.food_ratings.set(foods[i], ratings[i]);
            if (!this.highest_rated.has(cuisines[i]) ||
                ratings[i] > this.food_ratings.get(this.highest_rated.get(cuisines[i])) ||
                (ratings[i] === this.food_ratings.get(this.highest_rated.get(cuisines[i])) && foods[i] < this.highest_rated.get(cuisines[i]))) {
                this.highest_rated.set(cuisines[i], foods[i]);
            }
        }
    }

    changeRating(food, newRating) {
        let cuisine = "";
        for (const [key, value] of this.highest_rated.entries()) {
            if (value === food) {
                cuisine = key;
                break;
            }
        }
        this.food_ratings.set(food, newRating);
        for (const [key, value] of this.food_ratings.entries()) {
            if (this.highest_rated.get(cuisine) === food ||
                (newRating > value && cuisine === key) ||
                (newRating === value && food < key)) {
                this.highest_rated.set(cuisine, food);
            }
        }
    }

    highestRated(cuisine) {
        return this.highest_rated.get(cuisine);
    }
}
```


    The algorithm uses two hash tables (or dictionary/hash map depending on the language). The first one (`food_ratings`) stores the rating for each food in the system, and the second one (`highest_rated`) keeps track of the highest-rated food for each cuisine.

When initializing the object, we iterate through the input lists, set the initial ratings for each food in `food_ratings`, and then update the highest-rated food for each cuisine.

The `changeRating` method first finds the current cuisine for the given food by iterating through the `highest_rated` map. Then, we update the rating of that food in `food_ratings`. Finally, we check if the updated rating food should now be the highest-rated food for its cuisine and update it if necessary.

The `highestRated` method simply returns the highest-rated food (with ties broken by lexicographical order) for the input cuisine by looking up the `highest_rated` map.

